article.headline: East Carolina 71, Tulane 68
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- Brock Young scored 18 points and hit two free throws with 9 seconds left to help Eastern Carolina defeat Tulane 71-68 on Wednesday night. The Pirates, who led for the first 35 minutes took the lead for good, 63-62, on Jamar Abrams' dunk with 2:02 to play. David Booker's free throws pulled the Green Wave (7-16, 2-8 Conference USA) within 69-68 with 54 seconds to go, and they had a chance to take the lead after a missed 3 by the Pirates. However, Jordan Callahan turned the ball over with 10 seconds left and Young made his two foul shots to give East Carolina (8-16, 2-8) its first ever sweep over a C-USA opponent. The Pirates also defeated Tulane 61-46 on Jan 24. Young finished with 18 points and added Abrams 16 for the Pirates, who snapped a three-game losing streak. The Green Wave were led by Kendall Timmons with 16 points and Aaron Holmes with 15.
